cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the implementation of uplink HARQ in a Cloud-RAN architecture, which involves the networking and communication aspects of the system. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper analyzes the throughput and probability of error of different HARQ modes over a fading MIMO link. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the architecture of the Cloud-RAN system and proposes novel feedback strategies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the control and decision-making aspects of the HARQ process in the Cloud-RAN system. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the transmission and decoding of data in a wireless communication system.
